FBIS3-53739 "drnes012_n_94005" FBIS-NES-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 LEBANON Amal-Israel Clashes Occur in Southern Areas Amal Attacks, Israeli Shelling Continue NC1601104794 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1000 GMT 16 Jan 94 NC1601104794 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The Israeli forces continue to besiege the townships of Rumaysh, 'Ayta al-Sha'b, and 'Aramta. Our correspondent reports that enemy forces bombarded the approaches to al-Nabatiyah and Kafr Tibnit with mortars. Meanwhile, an Amal Movement group attacked enemy positions in Hula, using rockets and medium machine guns. A clash ensued for 10 minutes between the group and the enemy troops. Enemy helicopters flew over the scene of clashes. Another group attacked the occupation position in al-Shumariyah, inflicting heavy material losses on the position. Immediately afterward, the enemy forces shelled Zawtar al-Sharqiyah and Zawtar al-Gharbiyah.
